Directions:

Hot tea: Bring freshly drawn cold water to a rolling boil. Place 1 teabag for each desired

minutes. Pour into your cup; add milk and natural sweeteners to taste.

Iced Tea: (makes 1 qt/1L): Place 5 teabags into a teapot or heat resistant pitcher. Pour 1

with cold water. Garnish and sweeten to taste.

your serving pitcher straining the leaves. Add ice and top-up the pitcher with cold water. Gamish and sweeten to
taste. [A ule of thumb when preparing fresh brewed iced tea is to double the strength of hot tea since it will be
poured over ice and diluted with cold water). Please note that this tea may tend to go cloudy or ‘milky’ when
poured over ice; a perfectly normal characteristic of some high quality black teas and nothing to worry about!
